Hey Quiznos, one more suggestion for the next release: change the first animation of your service bay to use ModuleAnimateGeneric, e.g.:

    MODULE{    name = ModuleAnimateGeneric    animationName = CloseTop    startEventGUIName = Close Top Doors    endEventGUIName = Open Top Doors    actionGUIName = Toggle Bay Doors}

The issue is that FSanimateGeneric doesn't implement the IScalarModule interface that ModuleCargoBay needs to work, so things inside the bay don't actually get shielded. (Easy way to check: put in some deployable solar panels, bind them to an action group, and try to deploy them while the bay is closed. If they open, the bay isn't shielding anything.) I've tried to [**add IScalarModule to FSanimateGeneric**](https://github.com/snjo/Firespitter/issues/121), but haven't succeeded (and it doesn't seem to have caught the attention of anyone more experienced than I). In the meantime, you should just change that module. Thanks!
